cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the task of pixelwise semantic image labeling, which is a core problem in computer vision. The proposed approach involves the use of deep networks and probabilistic graphical models, which are typical techniques used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of hand-designed priors and label propagation also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) respectively. Finally, the paper experiments with two different datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
